WEBVTT

00:00.469 --> 00:02.084
- [Gordon] Tonight on Hotel Hell.

00:02.084 --> 00:03.785
In a small Connecticut town

00:03.785 --> 00:06.228
a family legacy is on
the brink of disaster.

00:06.228 --> 00:08.776
Do you think this is
what your father wanted?

00:08.776 --> 00:09.645
- Absolutely not.

00:09.645 --> 00:10.513
You're a mean horrible bitch.

00:10.513 --> 00:12.191
- [Gordon] A sibling rivalry has torn

00:12.191 --> 00:13.743
the Hardisty family apart.

00:13.743 --> 00:14.760
Not even love for each other,

00:14.760 --> 00:16.584
it is shocking.

00:16.584 --> 00:17.994
- She wants things done her way.

00:17.994 --> 00:19.626
- I'm in charge of the ship.

00:19.626 --> 00:20.732
- You give a fuck how long? -No my tray

00:20.732 --> 00:23.395
- [Gordon] With the owners
at each other's throats.

00:23.395 --> 00:25.011
- Shut the fuck up!

00:25.011 --> 00:26.502
- [Gordon] This once thriving country in

00:26.502 --> 00:28.548
may have to shut it's doors forever.

00:28.548 --> 00:30.135
Sell it!

00:30.135 --> 00:33.263
(upbeat rock music)

00:55.741 --> 00:58.370
(peaceful music)

00:58.370 --> 00:59.721
- [Gordon] In the heart
of Woodbury, Connecticut

00:59.721 --> 01:01.929
stands the state's oldest inn,

01:01.929 --> 01:03.792
the Curtis House.

01:03.792 --> 01:06.362
Opened in 1736, the 16 bedroom inn

01:06.362 --> 01:08.396
has been owned and run
by the Hardisty family

01:08.396 --> 01:10.360
for nearly 60 years

01:10.360 --> 01:11.682
and is currently being run

01:11.682 --> 01:14.474
by Chris Hardisty and his sister, T.J.

01:14.474 --> 01:19.688
- The Curtis House is
haunted, (door slams) see you.

01:20.822 --> 01:22.658
The rooms will all be
done and the comforters

01:22.658 --> 01:23.857
will be nice and neat and tidy.

01:23.857 --> 01:25.565
And you can go back in five
minutes later and it looks

01:25.565 --> 01:27.952
like somebody rolled across it.

01:27.952 --> 01:29.660
I would walk by a table
and two minutes later

01:29.660 --> 01:31.578
a plate would fly off of it.

01:31.578 --> 01:33.436
I went to light the fireplace and it blew

01:33.436 --> 01:35.608
up on me and I got burns.

01:37.474 --> 01:38.897
There are spirits here.

01:38.897 --> 01:40.918
- [Gordon] But spirits
aren't paying guests

01:40.918 --> 01:44.238
and the Curtis House bedrooms
are empty most nights.

01:44.238 --> 01:45.668
- Right now, I would say we're

01:45.668 --> 01:48.423
about a $100,000 in debt.

01:48.423 --> 01:50.323
My dad recently passed away.

01:50.323 --> 01:51.525
He had a firm belief

01:51.525 --> 01:53.937
that my brother and I
could take over the inn.

01:53.937 --> 01:58.307
It just left me more
determined to succeed.

01:58.307 --> 02:00.014
- [Gordon] Failing to continue
their father's success

02:00.014 --> 02:03.222
with the inn, has destroyed
Chris and T.J.'s relationship.

02:03.222 --> 02:06.021
They hardly ever speak, and
when they do, they fight.

02:06.021 --> 02:07.752
- [Chris] You're a mean, horrible bitch.

02:07.752 --> 02:09.757
If we were married we'd
probably be divorced by now.

02:09.757 --> 02:13.119
You've come off like this
every time, all the time.

02:13.119 --> 02:15.776
She's controlling, she
wants things done her way.

02:15.776 --> 02:17.946
- Because when I sit there and give a rule

02:17.946 --> 02:20.118
I want the rule followed.

02:21.795 --> 02:24.078
My brother frustrates me to
the point where sometimes

02:24.078 --> 02:27.427
I would like to just bop
him over the head to get rid

02:27.427 --> 02:28.931
of some frustrations.

02:28.931 --> 02:31.683
- Another woman that doesn't
listen to a fuckin thing I say.

02:31.683 --> 02:33.355
- [Gordon] Chris and T.J.s his
frustrations with each other

02:33.355 --> 02:38.397
and their failing business have
made the inn hell for staff.

02:38.397 --> 02:41.149
- [T.J.] No, my tray. No, my tray.

02:41.149 --> 02:42.423
- Well, I don't give a fuck!

02:42.423 --> 02:43.292
- They just don't care.

02:43.292 --> 02:44.828
If you look at your boss who doesn't care

02:44.828 --> 02:46.509
why are you gonna care?

02:46.509 --> 02:47.844
- T.J. is not a great leader.

02:47.844 --> 02:49.634
She yells at you, I've
never heard a thank you.

02:49.634 --> 02:50.502
Thank you.

02:50.502 --> 02:52.819
A thank you can go a long ways.

02:52.819 --> 02:54.832
- Chris. He's just a fat, lazy slob.

02:54.832 --> 02:56.042
- [Chris] There's shit everywhere.

02:56.042 --> 02:58.549
- We will get complaints from
the customers, we will have

02:58.549 --> 03:00.794
problems with dishes,
it's just shrugged off.

03:00.794 --> 03:02.615
He doesn't give a crap.

03:02.615 --> 03:05.256
- I've lost respect for
T.J. and Christopher.

03:05.256 --> 03:09.774
We've lost a lot of customers
because of management.

03:10.783 --> 03:12.978
- Since T.J. and Chris both took over,

03:12.978 --> 03:16.173
everything is going downhill.

03:16.173 --> 03:17.419
- [Male Guest] There's
a stain on my pillow.

03:17.419 --> 03:18.476
- [Female Guest] Disgusting.

03:18.476 --> 03:19.676
- [Male Guest] Look at this.

03:19.676 --> 03:22.745
- [Female Guest] Wow,
close the bathroom door.

03:22.745 --> 03:24.137
- [Male Guest] Like a rusted soap holder.

03:24.137 --> 03:26.670
- [Female Guest] Did you
have your tetanus shot?

03:26.670 --> 03:28.252
- Everything sucked.

03:28.252 --> 03:30.748
- Can you give me another
plate without ants on it?

03:30.748 --> 03:34.278
- I would never come here again.

03:34.278 --> 03:36.509
- [Gordon] If things
don't improve and fast

03:36.509 --> 03:39.032
a family legacy could
come to a tragic end.

03:39.032 --> 03:41.498
- The Curtis House is a
huge thing to our family.

03:41.498 --> 03:43.257
We've been here for 59 years.

03:43.257 --> 03:45.429
We've all pretty much grown up here.

03:45.429 --> 03:47.170
- Curtis House is like my second home.

03:47.170 --> 03:48.256
So it has been all these years.

03:48.256 --> 03:51.218
The same with my mother and my aunts.

03:51.218 --> 03:53.148
- If the Curtis House shut down

03:53.148 --> 03:58.101
it would really feel like we'd
lost a part of our family.

04:00.317 --> 04:02.127
- [Gordon] I'm on my
way to the Curtis House,

04:02.127 --> 04:03.990
It's Connecticut's oldest inn.

04:03.990 --> 04:05.861
I'm excited about it because
it's supposed to be one

04:05.861 --> 04:07.893
of New England's historical gems.

04:07.893 --> 04:11.054
There's nothing wrong
with being the oldest.

04:11.054 --> 04:14.111
Just depends how much Botox you've had.

04:14.111 --> 04:14.979
I'm going to be arriving

04:14.979 --> 04:18.163
on a big day for hotels and
restaurants across America.

04:18.163 --> 04:20.344
But there's something
I've got to do first.

04:20.344 --> 04:21.748
(phone ringing)

04:21.748 --> 04:22.750
- [Gordon's Mum] Hello?

04:22.750 --> 04:23.754
- Hi mum.

04:23.754 --> 04:25.034
- [Gordon's Mum] Oh, hi, how are you?

04:25.034 --> 04:26.248
- I'm very well, thank you.

04:26.248 --> 04:28.796
I'm just ringing you to
wish you happy Mother's Day.

04:28.796 --> 04:30.995
- [Gordon's Mum] Oh,
thank you so much Gordon.

04:30.995 --> 04:33.459
And your flowers were
lovely, thank you very much,

04:33.459 --> 04:34.605
very kind of you.

04:34.605 --> 04:36.062
- Well, I'm sorry can't be with you.

04:36.062 --> 04:37.461
- [Gordon's Mum] Thank
you so much for calling,

04:37.461 --> 04:38.688
it's really kind of you.

04:38.688 --> 04:39.657
- Well, listen, have a great day.

04:39.657 --> 04:40.629
Love you lots.

04:40.629 --> 04:41.745
- [Gordon's Mum] Love you, bye.

04:41.745 --> 04:42.613
- Bye now.

04:44.111 --> 04:45.513
Ah, great, here we are

04:45.513 --> 04:47.509
the Curtis House.

04:47.509 --> 04:50.463
Connecticut's oldest inn, lovely.

04:51.936 --> 04:54.242
The Happy Mother's Day
sign looks a bit crap

04:54.242 --> 04:56.953
but I suppose it's the
thought that counts.

04:56.953 --> 04:58.715
Look at this place.

04:58.715 --> 05:00.206
Built before 1736,

05:00.206 --> 05:01.162
incredible.

05:02.927 --> 05:03.796
- Hi there.

05:03.796 --> 05:04.884
- Gordon, nice to see you.

05:04.884 --> 05:06.037
- Oh, welcome to the Curtis House.

05:06.037 --> 05:06.905
- Happy Mother's Day.

05:06.905 --> 05:08.024
- Thank you very much.

05:08.024 --> 05:09.249
- And what's your first name?

05:09.249 --> 05:10.118
- Babe.

05:10.118 --> 05:11.462
- I know you're a babe,
but what's your name?

05:11.462 --> 05:12.331
- Shirley.

05:12.331 --> 05:14.001
- Shirley, nice to see you my darling.

05:14.001 --> 05:15.453
So it's Mother's Day,

05:15.453 --> 05:16.331
the restaurant's booked?

05:16.331 --> 05:17.200
- Yes.

05:17.200 --> 05:18.069
- So it's a big day, right?

05:18.069 --> 05:18.937
- Yes.

05:18.937 --> 05:19.806
- Is the hotel full?

05:19.806 --> 05:20.674
- Not tonight.

05:20.674 --> 05:21.990
- Oh, how many rooms are booked?

05:21.990 --> 05:23.378
- Just one.

05:23.378 --> 05:24.247
- Just one?

05:24.247 --> 05:25.115
- Yeah.

05:25.115 --> 05:25.984
Just me?

05:25.984 --> 05:26.931
- Yes.

05:26.931 --> 05:28.107
- So I'm a little bit early

05:28.107 --> 05:29.925
- Okay, usually check-in is three o'clock.

05:29.925 --> 05:30.794
- Three? Oh.

05:30.794 --> 05:34.087
- There's usually a $10 an hour fee.

05:34.087 --> 05:36.551
- That's what, four hours, so $40 already?

05:36.551 --> 05:37.642
- Yes.

05:37.642 --> 05:39.419
- So I could save a little bit of money

05:39.419 --> 05:41.429
by hanging out and not
actually going into the room?

05:41.429 --> 05:42.618
- Yes.

05:42.618 --> 05:44.688
- So I want to save myself 40 bucks.

05:44.688 --> 05:45.557
- Yes.

05:45.557 --> 05:48.063
- So if I just take a little nap.

05:48.063 --> 05:50.147
- What is he doing?

05:50.147 --> 05:51.583
Mr. Ramsay.

05:51.583 --> 05:52.838
(laughing)

05:52.838 --> 05:55.265
That's really not appropriate.

05:55.265 --> 05:56.916
Mr. Ramsay? Gordon?

05:57.944 --> 05:59.413
(snoring)

05:59.413 --> 06:00.716
This isn't very appropriate.

06:00.716 --> 06:02.201
- Oh, I'm sorry.

06:02.201 --> 06:03.287
- I'm sorry.

06:03.287 --> 06:05.301
- I'm a joking, but it doesn't make sense,

06:05.301 --> 06:07.323
you're charging me $10 a hour.

06:07.323 --> 06:09.883
If I just hang out on the
sofa, get a little blanket,

06:09.883 --> 06:12.038
I can save myself some money.

06:12.038 --> 06:13.048
- Yeah. This rule actually went

06:13.048 --> 06:15.971
into effect about six months
ago, this $10 an hour.

06:15.971 --> 06:19.774
- Oh really? And is it making
a big impact on the business?

06:19.774 --> 06:21.037
- People don't like it.

06:21.037 --> 06:23.790
The bookings in the rooms
have definitely gone downhill.

06:23.790 --> 06:25.363
I think they would be a lot busier if T.J.

06:25.363 --> 06:28.613
didn't have these ridiculous rules.

06:28.613 --> 06:31.353
- Is that right, my details
in here, credit card details?

06:31.353 --> 06:33.549
- Yes. We take a credit card
number to hold the room.

06:33.549 --> 06:35.559
- No, I appreciate that
but why put it in the book?

06:35.559 --> 06:37.175
- That's the house policy,
and if the customer insists,

06:37.175 --> 06:40.806
then we can erase it once they check out.

06:40.806 --> 06:43.236
- I got the credit card
details of everybody.

06:43.236 --> 06:46.278
- I will have to call nine one one.

06:47.215 --> 06:50.549
I don't really have to
call nine one one, do I?

06:50.549 --> 06:54.359
- Babe, see by the time you've
called nine one one, okay,

06:54.359 --> 06:57.767
I've hacked into every
credit card in this book

06:57.767 --> 07:00.758
and made myself a fortune,
so whose policy is this?

07:00.758 --> 07:01.626
It's a bit weird.

07:01.626 --> 07:04.345
- This is a house policy,
like T.J. likes it.

07:04.345 --> 07:05.213
- The owner?

07:05.213 --> 07:06.082
- Yes.

07:06.082 --> 07:07.484
- Would you not think there's
a security breach there?

07:07.484 --> 07:09.578
- Oh, I know, that's why
her policy is no one to look

07:09.578 --> 07:11.768
in this book except the desk person.

07:11.768 --> 07:12.721
- Wow, okay.

07:12.721 --> 07:15.020
- I can't believe you're
gonna be in room 16.

07:15.020 --> 07:16.438
- Why?

07:16.438 --> 07:19.617
- Because room 16 has a
ghost in it. (creepy music)

07:19.617 --> 07:21.848
This woman told me who went to room 16,

07:21.848 --> 07:24.267
she said the ghost was
pulling the blankets

07:24.267 --> 07:26.219
off her all night long.

07:26.219 --> 07:27.469
- And you haven't been drinking sherry?

07:27.469 --> 07:28.337
- No.

07:28.337 --> 07:29.275
- Wow.

07:29.275 --> 07:30.986
- Betty is a ghost at the Curtis House

07:30.986 --> 07:33.168
and people do tell us that she raises

07:33.168 --> 07:34.825
a little bit of havoc with them.

07:34.825 --> 07:37.644
She's definitely there.

07:37.644 --> 07:38.512
- Room 16.

07:43.279 --> 07:46.321
- The haunted room. My goodness me.

07:48.708 --> 07:52.362
What is that on there?
Is that a footprint?

07:52.362 --> 07:54.273
- C'mon, no way.

07:54.273 --> 07:56.229
- So what's all that
big scuff mark on there?

07:56.229 --> 07:59.023
- Yes, it looks like a footprint to me.

07:59.023 --> 08:01.709
- And what's that in there? Dead bugs.

08:01.709 --> 08:05.650
Oh dear, oh geez, look at this one here.

08:05.650 --> 08:07.384
- I give them a list of the
rooms that are coming in,

08:07.384 --> 08:09.616
they're supposed to
thoroughly check the room.

08:09.616 --> 08:13.507
- And what's? Do have
electricity in the house?

08:13.507 --> 08:15.864
- I couldn't believe what
Gordon found in that room.

08:15.864 --> 08:18.036
- And what is this? Oops.

08:21.369 --> 08:23.412
- Nobody just realised or cared.

08:23.412 --> 08:25.084
- How long have you been working here?

08:25.084 --> 08:27.398
- Off and on since about 1965.

08:27.398 --> 08:28.266
- How was it then?

08:28.266 --> 08:29.595
- Busy all the time.

08:29.595 --> 08:31.359
- Well 48 years, that's incredible

08:31.359 --> 08:32.761
so this place means a lot to you?

08:32.761 --> 08:34.174
- Oh yes, my second home.

08:34.174 --> 08:36.203
- Are you connected to
the family in any way?

08:36.203 --> 08:39.852
- T.J.'s parents and
my mother were cousins.

08:39.852 --> 08:42.913
- So it must be sad for
you to see it struggling?

08:42.913 --> 08:44.219
- Yes, definitely.

08:44.219 --> 08:45.210
- And why is it struggling?

08:45.210 --> 08:46.985
- It's the way our two bosses get along.

08:46.985 --> 08:48.552
- And was it different when

08:48.552 --> 08:49.615
T.J. and Chris's parents were running it?

08:49.615 --> 08:52.122
- Oh yeah, much more professional.

08:52.122 --> 08:54.223
- So why do you stay and
why'd you put up with this?

08:54.223 --> 08:56.193
- I take pride in this
place, I like this place.

08:56.193 --> 08:57.062
- I can see that.

08:57.062 --> 08:58.484
- I really do but they don't understand

08:58.484 --> 09:01.226
that the place is really worth it.

09:01.226 --> 09:02.507
I really think T.J. and Chris

09:02.507 --> 09:05.035
are really hurting the business.

09:05.035 --> 09:08.385
Somebody needs to knock
some sense into them.

09:08.385 --> 09:10.801
- First impressions, dismal.

09:10.801 --> 09:13.497
All my credit card details
downstairs in that book

09:13.497 --> 09:14.977
in such a vulnerable position.

09:14.977 --> 09:17.059
One of the busiest weekends
ever for this hotel

09:17.059 --> 09:20.035
with Mother's Day, I'm the
only one staying in the hotel,

09:20.035 --> 09:21.663
that's, that's not good.

09:21.663 --> 09:24.293
Dust everywhere and a
window sill full of bugs.

09:24.293 --> 09:26.306
I don't think we would get
possessed staying here,

09:26.306 --> 09:29.175
I think we're gonna get a disease.

09:29.175 --> 09:33.656
Right, go to the stairs,
have a look. (creepy music)

09:33.656 --> 09:35.046
Hey, let me out!

09:36.212 --> 09:38.764
Honestly, it must be the bloody ghost.

09:38.764 --> 09:40.920
Come on Betty, let me out!

09:40.920 --> 09:42.623
I just wanna get some lunch.

09:42.623 --> 09:45.776
(creepy music)

09:45.776 --> 09:47.198
- I've just arrived at the Curtis House

09:47.198 --> 09:48.592
in Woodbury, Connecticut.

09:48.592 --> 09:50.293
And they've given me a room with a ghost,

09:50.293 --> 09:52.406
and a door lock that doesn't work.

09:52.406 --> 09:53.441
At last!

09:53.441 --> 09:55.407
I'm the only guest in this hotel

09:55.407 --> 09:57.305
despite the fact it's Mother's Day

09:57.305 --> 09:59.006
and the restaurant is fully booked.

09:59.006 --> 10:02.882
What a dreadful missed opportunity.

10:02.882 --> 10:03.750
- Hello.

10:03.750 --> 10:04.619
- Good afternoon.

10:04.619 --> 10:05.487
- How are you?

10:05.487 --> 10:06.399
Welcome to Curtis House, I'm
doing well sir, how about you?

10:06.399 --> 10:07.267
And this is?

10:07.267 --> 10:08.136
- Hi, my name is T.J.

10:08.136 --> 10:09.004
- T.J.?

10:09.004 --> 10:09.873
- Nice to meet you sir.

10:09.873 --> 10:11.175
- The owner? -Yes

10:11.175 --> 10:12.044
- [Both] Nice to see you.

10:12.044 --> 10:12.912
This is my mother.

10:12.912 --> 10:13.928
- Happy Mother's Day.

10:13.928 --> 10:14.797
- Thanks very much.

10:14.797 --> 10:15.665
- It's an absolute honour to meet you,

10:15.665 --> 10:17.197
are you working today?

10:17.197 --> 10:20.187
- I have worked every
holiday and never got paid!

10:20.187 --> 10:23.047
- Ridiculous. You should
be sat having lunch,

10:23.047 --> 10:24.713
enjoying this business.

10:24.713 --> 10:26.317
Shall we go to the table?

10:26.317 --> 10:27.414
- We shall.

10:27.414 --> 10:29.501
- Time for me to see if
the hotels restaurants

10:29.501 --> 10:31.361
is as bad as the bedrooms.

10:31.361 --> 10:32.230
Right.

10:33.245 --> 10:35.236
- Hi, my name's Karen.
I'll be taking care of you.

10:35.236 --> 10:36.104
- Are you connected to the family?

10:36.104 --> 10:38.246
- Yes, I am, aunt T.J.
and uncle Chris's niece.

10:38.246 --> 10:39.834
- Okay, nice,

10:39.834 --> 10:42.991
and just in a nutshell,
what's wrong with the place?

10:42.991 --> 10:46.110
- Now, there's no communication
between my aunt and uncle.

10:46.110 --> 10:47.496
It's gotten a million times worse

10:47.496 --> 10:49.035
since my grandfather passed away.

10:49.035 --> 10:50.124
- It shows, doesn't it?

10:50.124 --> 10:50.992
- Yeah.

10:50.992 --> 10:51.971
I asked Gordon to come here

10:51.971 --> 10:54.130
because my family
desperately needs his help.

10:54.130 --> 10:56.564
They've been struggling for way too long.

10:56.564 --> 10:58.316
They don't know what to do.

10:58.316 --> 10:59.718
We really need his help.

10:59.718 --> 11:02.015
This is the dinner menu.

11:02.015 --> 11:04.936
- Wow. What would you say, crab cakes?

11:04.936 --> 11:07.470
- The crab cakes, yeah, you, yes.

11:07.470 --> 11:09.560
- Ah, don't look at me like
that, that slight hesitation.

11:09.560 --> 11:11.000
- They're hit or miss, they-

11:11.000 --> 11:11.912
- They're hot or miss?

11:11.912 --> 11:12.781
- Yeah.

11:12.781 --> 11:14.076
The crab cakes, what else?

11:14.076 --> 11:15.256
I'll take some calamari.

11:15.256 --> 11:16.125
- Okay.

11:16.125 --> 11:17.226
- And join us for a little
taste of the burger.

11:17.226 --> 11:18.185
- How do you like it cooked?

11:18.185 --> 11:19.054
- Medium rare please.

11:19.054 --> 11:19.922
- Medium rare.

